<HEADER>
A7681 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-HKN-KINGNOT-LADN-(SLA     03-20 0316
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HKN-KINGNOT-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DUCHESNE PLAYS WAITING GAME
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGER PHILLIPS  
 c.1999 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
<TEXT>
<P>
   INGLEWOOD, Calif. _ Steve Duchesne remained in hockey limbo
Friday, a King for at least another day.
</P>
<P>
   Duchesne cleared NHL waivers, which was no surprise because if a
team had claimed him, it would have had to pay his $7.5 million
salary the next two years.
</P>
<P>
   The 33-year-old rushing defenseman indicated that waiting for a
resolution has been difficult. He might have to wait a few days
more.
</P>
<P>
   The NHL trading deadline is Tuesday and Duchesne could be dealt
by then, or could remain with the Kings if they are unable to
strike a deal. It appears the Kings would be willing to assume some
of Duchesne's contract to unload a player who has been the biggest
disappointment in a disappointing season.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm kind of going day by day right now,'' Duchesne said. ``I'm
trying not to think too far ahead.''
</P>
<P>
   Duchesne's agent, Pat Brisson, said Thursday that Kings general
manager Dave Taylor spoke to him in January, expressing concerns
with Duchesne's performance. Brisson said Taylor informed him three
weeks ago that the Kings were trying to trade Duchesne.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's unfortunate things didn't work out,'' Brisson said.
``It's their decision. In my opinion, it's a little premature. But
it's their decision.''
</P>
<P>
   Among the teams that might be looking for a defenseman with
Duchesne's offensive skills are Carolina and Philadelphia. The
Kings play host to Florida tonight at the Forum.
</P>
<P>
   __ Loose pucks: An MRI revealed that forward Sean Pronger
suffered a torn medial collateral ligament in his left knee in a
first-period collision Thursday night. He'll be sidelined four to
six weeks. Vladimir Tsyplakov, who has missed the last month with a
knee injury, is expected to replace Pronger in the lineup.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-03-20-99 0020EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
