<HEADLINE>
GALAXY MIGHT OPEN WITHOUT CIENFUEGOS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By FRED J. ROBLEDO  
 c.1999 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PASADENA, Calif. _ Galaxy coach Octavio Zambrano said late
Friday that Mauricio Cienfuegos met with league officials to
discuss his contract dispute with Major League Soccer, but he won't
know until this morning if the three-time All-Star will be with the
Galaxy for tonight's season opener against Colorado at the Rose
Bowl.
</P>
<P>
   Cienfuegos, a holdout since training camp began in February,
joined the team Tuesday in what he called a ``good faith'' effort,
hoping to increase his chances for a substantial raise to his
$103,000 contract.
</P>
<P>
   Cienfuegos met with Ivan Gazidis, executive vice president of
player relations for the MLS, in the office of his agent, Corey
Clemetson, but Clemetson said the meeting ``didn't go well.''
</P>
<P>
   Clemetson said Cienfuegos told him and Univision that he and
fellow countryman Raul Diaz Arce, a holdout with San Jose, would
not play tonight.
</P>
<P>
   ``Mauricio stated that as of right now he's not playing,''
Clemetson said. ``He felt the offer (by the league) didn't make
sense for him. He's very disappointed but sticking with what he
said, which is not to play.''
</P>
<P>
   Cienfuegos will meet with MLS commissioner Doug Logan this
morning without Clemetson in hopes of securing an agreement before
tonight's 7:30 match. But Clemetson said an agreement is unlikely.
</P>
<P>
   ``His meeting with Logan isn't a negotiation,'' Clemetson said.
``They are getting together to discuss his situation ... but who
knows? If things change in less than a 24-hour period, maybe he
would reconsider, but right now he's decided not to play on
Saturday.''
</P>
<P>
   Cienfuegos threatened on Tuesday that if a contract wasn't
worked out, he would fly back to his native El Salvador.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think something positive will come out of this meeting
tomorrow,'' an optimistic Zambrano said. ``If he signs he will
play, obviously. If he doesn't, I'm not sure what's going to
happen.''
</P>
<P>
   Clemetson said he's not sure what Cienfuegos will do.
</P>
<P>
   ``The fair thing to say is I don't know,'' Clemetson said.
``Right now, Mauricio is very upset. I think a number of things can
happen, but we'll just have to wait and see.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-03-20-99 0104EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
