<SLUG> BC-BKC-TEMPLE-PURDUE-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
AFTER ROUTING PURDUE, TEMPLE FACES DUKE 
</HEADLINE>
  (js) 
 By JOE DRAPE   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. _ The Temple Owls turned two Purdue
technical fouls into a 10-point swing on Friday and had one of
their best shooting performances of the year to drum the
Boilermakers, 77-55, and reach the East Regional final.
</P>
<P>
   It will be Temple's fourth appearance in the final eight in 11
years and a rematch of the 1987 game that the Owls lost to Duke,
63-53. The sixth-seeded Owls were down by 11-10 when Purdue guard
Jaraan Cornell and then Coach Gene Keady were slapped with
technical fouls. Cornell was caught retaliating in a scuffle with
Temple's Quincy Wadley, and Keady argued the call.
</P>
<P>
   The Owls made five free throws, a shot in the lane and a
3-pointer to go ahead by 20-10. But it was the Owls' 52.7 percent
shooting that kept the 10th-seeded Boilermakers from leading again.
``Those things happen,'' said Keady, whose team shot 45.2 percent
and finished 21-13. ``We could never sustain anything from there.''
</P>
<P>
   The Owls (24-10) were led by Mark Karcher, who had 21 points,
including 15 from beyond the 3-point line. Karcher, who scored a
combined 11 points in victories against Kent and Cincinnati, was 8
of 17 from the field.
</P>
<P>
   ``The last two games I wasn't aggressive on offense,'' said the
sophomore forward. ``I told myself I was going to come out and take
the open shot. ''
</P>
<P>
   Temple's match-up zone frustrated the Boilermakers, who were
outrebounded by 31-23 and outscored on second-chance points by
20-6. They committed 20 turnovers that led to 36 points for the
Owls, while Temple's back court of Pepe Sanchez and Rasheed
Brokenborough took care of the ball and combined for 25 points.
</P>
<P>
   ``We played very tough defense and I'm pleased with that,'' said
Temple Coach John Chaney. ``We can never count on our offense to be
that good, but our kids will always play defense.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
