<HEADLINE>
COWBOYS RAISE TICKET PRICES
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CLARENCE E. HILL JR. 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ It is unknown whether speedy receiver Raghib
Ismail will be a Cowboys player in 1999.
</P>
<P>
   What is clear is that fans will pay more to watch the Cowboys at
Texas Stadium next season, with or without Ismail.
</P>
<P>
   Ticket prices have increased an average of 10.1 percent from
last year in the price list released yesterday.
</P>
<P>
   Cowboys owner Jerry Jones was unavailable to comment.
</P>
<P>
   In 1998, the average ticket price for a seat at Texas Stadium
was $45.01. The new average price for all seats, including luxury
suites, is $49.54. For nonluxury suite seats, which are roughly 89
percent of the stadium's capacity, the average price will increase
to $47.91 from $43.58 last season.
</P>
<P>
   Since 1980, the club has changed ticket prices almost every two
years with an average price increase of 17.1 percent. Since Jones
bought the team in 1989, this is the sixth price change, at an
average increase of 11.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
   In addition to the traditional matchups against NFC East foes,
the 1999 home schedule features matchups against the NFC champion
Atlanta Falcons, the New York Jets, the Green Bay Packers and the
Miami Dolphins.
COWBOYS RE-SIGN TWO
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys re-signed punter Toby Gowin and defensive tackle
Nathan Davis to one-year contracts, bringing to six the number of
the Cowboys' exclusive-rights free agents with new deals.
</P>
<P>
   The team previously reached deals with linebackers Nate Hemsley,
Brandon Tolbert and Robert Thomas and quarterback Mike Quinn. Still
unsigned are kicker Richie Cunningham, safety Singor Mobley and
center Mike Kiselak. nn
</P>
</TEXT>
