<HEADLINE>
MARIAN SEARCHINGER THEATRICAL AGENT, 81 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (ATTN: Calif., N.Y.)  (js) 
 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Marian Searchinger, a New York theatrical agent, died on Monday
at a convalescent home in Santa Barbara, Calif. She was 81.
</P>
<P>
   Ms. Searchinger's clients included such actors as Ossie Davis,
Ruby Dee and Jane Alexander, the television writer Ernest Kinoy and
the directors Franklin Schaffner and Fielder Cook. She also
represented the poet Langston Hughes, the lyricist Hal David and
the playwright Roger Hirson. She worked as an agent at Creative
Management Associates (now International Creative Management) from
the 1950s to the early '80s, and then joined NBC, where she worked
on literary acquisitions and daytime programming.
</P>
<P>
   She is survived by her husband, Gene; a daughter, Jill; two
sons, Brian and Tim, and a sister, Renee Cohen.  &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
