<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BUDGET-AUSTERITY-REVIEW-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
I'M THE FISCAL PURIST. NO, I AM. 
</HEADLINE>
   (The Week in Review)  
 (NOTE TO INTERNATIONAL CLIENTS: For international clients' use by
special arrangement only. Asian and European points: contact Karl
Horwitz in Paris for details and prices (Phone: 47 42 17 11; FAX:
47-42-80-44). Latin American points: contact Olivia Vasquez in Los
Angeles (Phone: 310-996-0075; FAX: 310-996-0089)  
 (bl)  
 By RICHARD W. STEVENSON   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ The federal budget deficit is history, and the
strong economy is generating surpluses that could last for decades.
But in Washington, pledges of budgetary austerity are emanating
from both parties in a way they never did when the outlook was
bleak.
</P>
