 &HT;    NHL notes
 &HT;    By Jeff Schultz
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Thrashers update: IceForum owner Jack Burton was
thrilled when Thrashers general manager Don Waddell announced that
all practices at the team's Duluth practice facility will be open
to the public next season. ``That's really good news, because I'm
going to build a restaurant and bar overlooking the Thrashers'
practice rink,'' he said. ... Construction on the facility, which
will include workout facilities, locker room and team offices,
probably will begin next week. Installation of a second rink is
scheduled for June. Both projects are slated to be completed by
late August. The Thrashers are scheduled to open training camp
Sept. 4 and plan to have part of camp at the IceForum. But they
might start camp in Orlando, at the facility shared by the NBA's
Magic and the IHL's Solar Bears, Atlanta's minor-league affiliate.
... At the groundbreaking, team vice president Dave Maggard said,
``We have several shovels here so we can accelerate the
construction.'' ... Waddell on the open practices: ``This is an
opportunity for the people to come out and see the players and get
autographs. Our players will be part of this community. They'll
live in the area, and this is pretty much going to be our home from
day to day.''
</P>
<P>
   POLICE BLOTTER
