<P>
   TWO MINUTES: CHRIS PRONGER
</P>
<P>
   _ Team, position: St. Louis, defenseman.
</P>
<P>
   _ Update: Leads NHL in minutes per game (30.2). Has career-high
38 points in 52 games.
</P>
<P>
   _ On recent win over struggling Flyers: ``We just tried to stay
in their face all night and not give their big guns a chance to
pick up speed. I think that's something a lot of teams have been
doing.''
</P>
<P>
   _ On the March 23 trading deadline: ``I kind of get excited.
It's fun to see what different teams are going to do. But
certainly, there is a lot of uncertainty in the dressing room,
players not knowing whether they're going to be traded or not. When
it's over, a lot of guys kind of take a deep breath.''
</P>
<P>
   _ On the Blues' inconsistency: ``Hopefully, we can fix that
going into the playoffs. We don't have the same talent as Detroit
or Colorado or Dallas, but I don't think we can't beat those
teams.''
</P>
<P>
   _ On the Blues being short-handed 79 more times than on the
power play: ``A lot of times, we're a perimeter team, and, if you
don't drive the net, it's hard to draw penalties. If you're tripped
in the corner, it's a little different than if you're coming out
with a scoring opportunity.''
</P>
