   COXNET FOCUS 0319: FOCUS _ In the fall of 1994, President
Clinton confounded his critics by successfully using 20,000
U.S.-led forces to overthrow a brutal military regime here and give
democracy a second chance. Almost no blood was shed and a triumph
in foreign policy was declared. But today, after nearly five years
of pouring more than $2.2 billion of American taxpayers' money into
Haiti, there is little to feel triumphant about. (Emling, Cox
Washington Bureau) Art includes a 3-column color photo showing two
young girls walking through the squalor of Haiti, and a 2-column
photo showing goods being delivered in a Haitian harbor.
